                >Healthy Eating for Kids and Teens</a
              >
              by the American Heart Association
            </li>
          </ul>
          <h1 style="margin-top: 2rem">Regular Exercise:</h1>
          <p>
            Regular exercise during puberty is important for maintaining a
            healthy weight, building muscle and bone strength, and reducing
            stress and anxiety. It's recommended that teenagers aim for at least
            60 minutes of moderate-intensity physical activity each day, such as
            brisk walking, cycling, swimming, or playing team sports.
            Strength-training exercises, such as push-ups or weightlifting, can
            also be beneficial for building muscle and bone strength. It's
            important to find activities that are enjoyable and sustainable, and
            to take rest days as needed to avoid injury.
          </p>
          <h3>Resources for Exercise</h3>
