            </li>
          </ul>
          <h1 style="margin-top: 2rem">Emotional Support:</h1>
          <p>
            Puberty can be a challenging time emotionally, as teenagers may
            experience mood swings, anxiety, and depression. It's important for
            teenagers to have a support system of family, friends, or a mental
            health professional to talk to and get support from. Practicing
            stress-reducing techniques, such as mindfulness, meditation, or
            journaling, can also help manage emotions and improve mental
            well-being. It's important for teenagers to prioritize their mental
            health and seek help if they are struggling.
          </p>
          <h3>Resources for Emotional support</h3>
